      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Although injury incidents with tractors and other farm machinery occurred more frequently in the farm yard or fields, public right-of-way was the third most frequent environment for Iowa tractor-related injuries during 1992 (Iowa Department of Public Health, 1993) . Fifteen percent of all tractor-related injuries occurred on a public roadway. During 1992, 59% of Iowa agricultural work-related injuries caused by motor vehicles involved in farm work occurred on public right-of-way. [CITATION_1] investigated 131 Iowa tractor-related fatality events that occurred from 1988 through 1992."
